'''''Harmozica ravergiensis''''' is a [[species]] of an air-breathing [[land snail]], a [[terrestrial animal|terrestrial]] [[pulmonate]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the family [[Hygromiidae]], the hairy snails and their allies.

This is the [[type species]] of the genus ''[[Harmozica (gastropod)|Harmozica]]''.<ref>[http://www.animalbase.uni-goettingen.de/zooweb/servlet/AnimalBase/home/genustaxon?id=2668 "Genus taxon summary for ''Harmozica''"]. AnimalBase, accessed May 2, 2014.</ref>

The [[specific name (zoology)|specific name]] ''ravergiensis'' is in honour of Mr. [[M. Ravergie]].<ref name="Férussac 1835"/><!-- qui nous  l'a envoyée de Tiflis =? that we send to Tbilisi -->

== Distribution ==
The distribution of this species is [[Caucasus|Caucasian]]<ref name="Balashov 2013"/> and countries include:
* probably non-native in [[List of non-marine molluscs of Ukraine|Ukraine]].<ref name="Balashov 2013"/>
** southeastern Ukraine in [[Dnipropetrovsk Oblast]] and [[Donetsk Oblast]] since 2006<ref name="Balashov 2013">Balashov I. A., Kramarenko S. S., Zhukov A. V., Shklyaruk A. N., Baidashnikov A. A. & Vasyliuk A. V. (2013). "Contribution to the knowledge of terrestrial molluscs in southeastern Ukraine". ''[[Malacologica Bohemoslovaca]]'' '''12''': 62-69. [http://mollusca.sav.sk/pdf/12/12.Balashov.pdf PDF].</ref>
** western Ukraine<ref name="Balashov 2013"/>
* [[List of non-marine molluscs of Armenia|Armenia]]<ref name="caucasus 2014">[http://www.caucasus-snails.uni-hamburg.de/CaucasianLandSnails-Dateien/Checklist.html "Caucasian Land Snails"]. accessed May 2, 2014.</ref>
* [[List of non-marine molluscs of Azerbaijan|Azerbaijan]]<ref name="caucasus 2014"/>
* [[List of non-marine molluscs of Georgia|Georgia]]<ref name="caucasus 2014"/>
* [[List of non-marine molluscs of Russia|Russia]]<ref name="caucasus 2014"/>

The type locality is "Caucasus".<ref name="AB ravergiensis"/>

== Description ==
The shape of the shell of ''Harmozica ravergiensis'' is globose.
